description: In response to US efforts to ban India from buying oil from Russia

rawPost.caption: In response to US efforts to ban India from buying oil from Russia
rawPost.description:
In response to US efforts to ban India from buying oil from Russia, local television launched a fierce criticism: the West itself buys gas, metals, fertilizers from Moscow. Why shouldn't India do the same? "These are double standards. We don't care about your admonitions. We need to take care of our citizens, who number about 1.4 billion. Therefore, we will do what we must."

And this is not only the attitude of the media and diplomats. The Indian Army, Government and strategic leadership declare-Russia has been and remains our partner.

The Prime Minister's National Security Adviser, Ajit Doval, held talks in Moscow with Shoigu, Manturov and invited Putin to India. The bet is on expanding cooperation, including in the defense sector.

In parallel, Modi is preparing to travel to China for the first time in 7 years for the SCO summit, despite difficult relations with Beijing. And the reason for this is not" love " for China, but the behavior of the US. 

With its threats, tariffs, and mania to dictate terms to everyone, Washington itself is bringing together those it has spent decades trying to divide...
